1
00:01:29,320 --> 00:01:32,000
=Our Days=

2
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:34,720
(Adapted from Lang Lang's original novel
"The Prime of the Goddess")

3
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:38,160
=Episode 23=

4
00:01:38,600 --> 00:01:39,721
I didn't harbor any ill intentions
toward you, right?

5
00:01:39,721 --> 00:01:41,281
Why are you harming me?

6
00:01:43,960 --> 00:01:44,760
Li Shu.

7
00:01:45,801 --> 00:01:47,441
Firstly, I have no idea

8
00:01:47,600 --> 00:01:48,801
about the anonymous letter
you talked about.

9
00:01:51,240 --> 00:01:53,120
I won't jump

10
00:01:53,201 --> 00:01:54,600
to such conclusions easily

11
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:56,480
before I can confirm

12
00:01:56,921 --> 00:01:57,880
that you've become

13
00:01:57,921 --> 00:01:58,960
the third wheel
between me and my husband.

14
00:01:59,680 --> 00:02:00,441
Secondly,

15
00:02:02,081 --> 00:02:04,921
if you did shatter my family,

16
00:02:06,281 --> 00:02:08,040
I would write an open letter
about your deeds

17
00:02:08,841 --> 00:02:10,040
instead of an anonymous letter.

18
00:02:10,040 --> 00:02:11,281
I'm not that cheap.

19
00:02:11,680 --> 00:02:13,040
You're not that cheap, huh?

20
00:02:13,841 --> 00:02:14,841
If so, why did you install

21
00:02:14,880 --> 00:02:16,080
a surveillance camera at home
after hiring me back?

22
00:02:16,841 --> 00:02:19,121
Why did you monitor Gao Ping
on apps, then?

23
00:02:20,681 --> 00:02:22,001
Are you done?

24
00:02:22,800 --> 00:02:24,281
Now, you're talking about
my family affair?

25
00:02:25,961 --> 00:02:26,961
I can even install

26
00:02:27,001 --> 00:02:28,200
100 surveillance cameras in my house

27
00:02:28,920 --> 00:02:29,961
as long as I'm happy.

28
00:02:30,441 --> 00:02:31,480
That's my house.

29
00:02:33,001 --> 00:02:35,600
As for Gao Ping, he's mine.

30
00:02:35,681 --> 00:02:36,640
He's my husband.

31
00:02:38,001 --> 00:02:39,401
I have the right to know where he is

32
00:02:39,760 --> 00:02:40,961
when I want to.

33
00:02:41,760 --> 00:02:43,080
As for what you guys think about me,

34
00:02:44,241 --> 00:02:45,281
that's your own business.

35
00:02:45,521 --> 00:02:46,961
You're still using that term, huh?

36
00:02:48,001 --> 00:02:48,800
That means you suspect

37
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:50,561
that Gao Ping
and I have an affair, am I right?

38
00:02:50,721 --> 00:02:51,721
It's best if that's not true.

39
00:02:52,521 --> 00:02:53,841
Li Shu, if you two do have an affair,

40
00:02:53,961 --> 00:02:55,161
I'll surely investigate it thoroughly.

41
00:02:55,681 --> 00:02:57,121
You've already affected my work.

42
00:02:58,561 --> 00:02:59,441
Sitong,

43
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:01,281
send Ms. Li to the elevator.

44
00:03:01,360 --> 00:03:02,721
No matter who wrote
that anonymous letter,

45
00:03:03,281 --> 00:03:04,320
I will hire an attorney.

46
00:03:04,760 --> 00:03:05,521
That's for the best.

47
00:03:20,080 --> 00:03:21,441
Good morning, Flowey.

48
00:03:21,640 --> 00:03:22,640
Good morning, Grace.

49
00:03:26,281 --> 00:03:26,920
You don't need to wait for me.

50
00:03:27,001 --> 00:03:27,721
You should leave first.

51
00:03:27,841 --> 00:03:28,360
It's fine.

52
00:03:28,401 --> 00:03:29,521
It's still early.

53
00:03:29,600 --> 00:03:30,401
Let's walk together.

54
00:03:33,521 --> 00:03:34,800
How did you manage

55
00:03:34,841 --> 00:03:35,561
to get a shared bike?

56
00:03:35,600 --> 00:03:36,961
There's always none
whenever I reach the station.

57
00:03:37,320 --> 00:03:37,760
Is that so?

58
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:39,800
I couldn't get one
in the past few days either.

59
00:03:39,880 --> 00:03:40,561
I don't know why,

60
00:03:40,600 --> 00:03:41,401
but for some reason,

61
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:42,841
there's always one bike

62
00:03:42,920 --> 00:03:44,200
at the station whenever I'm there.

63
00:03:44,281 --> 00:03:45,561
Maybe I'm just lucky.

64
00:03:45,961 --> 00:03:47,521
If so, I guess you're too lucky.

65
00:03:47,880 --> 00:03:49,360
I hope I can be lucky all the time.

66
00:03:50,001 --> 00:03:50,920
Have you taken breakfast?

67
00:03:50,961 --> 00:03:51,360
Not yet.

68
00:03:51,401 --> 00:03:51,841
What about you?

69
00:03:52,200 --> 00:03:53,001
I haven't taken breakfast either.

70
00:03:53,001 --> 00:03:53,800
Let's get some breakfast later.

71
00:03:55,640 --> 00:03:56,480
I'll go up first.

72
00:03:56,480 --> 00:03:57,241
Alright. See you later.

73
00:03:57,241 --> 00:03:57,721
Goodbye.

74
00:04:02,200 --> 00:04:02,841
Hello?

75
00:04:02,920 --> 00:04:03,640
Are you Xiang Zhong?

76
00:04:04,360 --> 00:04:05,360
I'm Deng Haiyang's friend.

77
00:04:06,600 --> 00:04:07,241
Hello.

78
00:04:07,561 --> 00:04:08,241
What's wrong?

79
00:04:08,681 --> 00:04:09,880
Deng Haiyang is in huge trouble.

80
00:04:11,080 --> 00:04:12,040
What happened?

81
00:04:24,120 --> 00:04:24,800
Xiang Zhong!

82
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:28,881
I'm Haiyang's friend, the person

83
00:04:28,961 --> 00:04:29,961
who called you just now.

84
00:04:30,240 --> 00:04:31,281
You can call me Ling.

85
00:04:31,521 --> 00:04:32,281
Nice to meet you.

86
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:35,281
Deng Haiyang just posted this
on his WeChat Moments.

87
00:04:35,521 --> 00:04:37,161
He recalled it after a few minutes.

88
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:38,240
Luckily, I took a screenshot.

89
00:04:38,241 --> 00:04:39,880
(Deng Haiyang: Goodbye.)

90
00:04:40,881 --> 00:04:41,440
He's trying

91
00:04:41,440 --> 00:04:42,761
to bid farewell to the world.

92
00:04:44,961 --> 00:04:45,920
This can't be.

93
00:04:46,881 --> 00:04:48,281
You said you couldn't
get in touch with him.

94
00:04:48,321 --> 00:04:49,841
If so, I'm sure I can't
get in touch with him either.

95
00:04:50,680 --> 00:04:51,920
But he's in Shanghai now.

96
00:04:52,721 --> 00:04:53,721
What is he doing in Shanghai?

97
00:04:54,721 --> 00:04:55,521
I've already asked him about it.

98
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:57,240
He wasn't willing to tell me.

99
00:04:58,560 --> 00:04:59,521
Actually, I know

100
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:01,081
that he escaped to Shanghai.

101
00:05:03,641 --> 00:05:05,401
He has received a huge blow lately.

102
00:05:06,240 --> 00:05:07,641
Forget about the divorce for now.

103
00:05:08,281 --> 00:05:09,360
Due to that incident,

104
00:05:09,761 --> 00:05:10,800
everyone in the world knows

105
00:05:10,841 --> 00:05:11,881
that he's a scam victim now.

106
00:05:12,281 --> 00:05:13,321
Which incident?

107
00:05:14,560 --> 00:05:15,440
Don't you know?

108
00:05:17,281 --> 00:05:18,800
Haiyang's scam case was solved.

109
00:05:19,081 --> 00:05:20,841
The TV station reached out to him
for an interview.

110
00:05:21,360 --> 00:05:22,360
His interview was already aired.

111
00:05:26,321 --> 00:05:27,480
Wouldn't the news

112
00:05:27,641 --> 00:05:29,281
blur the faces of those
who were involved?

113
00:05:29,440 --> 00:05:30,321
They did.

114
00:05:30,600 --> 00:05:31,721
But those who know him

115
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:33,240
can tell that it's him at first glance.

116
00:05:34,641 --> 00:05:35,321
Then what's the point

117
00:05:35,360 --> 00:05:36,360
of protecting the people involved.

118
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:38,240
Don't be frustrated at me.

119
00:05:38,841 --> 00:05:40,401
I'm not the one who censored it.

120
00:05:42,120 --> 00:05:43,281
According to your understanding of him,

121
00:05:43,841 --> 00:05:45,000
do you think he's that kind of person?

122
00:05:47,641 --> 00:05:48,680
What kind of person?

123
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:51,680
The kind who will end their lives.

124
00:05:57,401 --> 00:05:58,560
I don't know either.

125
00:05:59,240 --> 00:06:01,600
Mr. Wang, look.

126
00:06:01,641 --> 00:06:02,440
It's almost lunchtime.

127
00:06:02,480 --> 00:06:03,600
Why don't we have lunch

128
00:06:03,641 --> 00:06:04,321
together later?

129
00:06:05,081 --> 00:06:06,440
Mr. Chai, you're too courteous.

130
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:07,321
Don't mention it.

131
00:06:07,440 --> 00:06:07,761
Yuanyuan,

132
00:06:07,961 --> 00:06:09,600
The restaurant has been booked, right?

133
00:06:09,721 --> 00:06:10,440
That's right.

134
00:06:10,761 --> 00:06:12,201
You can head there with Mr. Wang

135
00:06:12,240 --> 00:06:12,800
and Mr. Liu first.

136
00:06:12,920 --> 00:06:13,521
I need to do something.

137
00:06:13,521 --> 00:06:14,521
I'll head there later, okay?

138
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:15,401
Okay.

139
00:06:15,440 --> 00:06:16,081
See you guys later.

140
00:06:16,120 --> 00:06:17,081
Mr. Chai, see you later.

141
00:06:17,120 --> 00:06:17,961
Alright. Goodbye. Good job.

142
00:06:17,961 --> 00:06:18,721
See you guys later.

143
00:06:19,081 --> 00:06:19,560
See you guys later.

144
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:20,161
Over here, please.

145
00:06:22,401 --> 00:06:23,161
So,

146
00:06:23,560 --> 00:06:25,040
you're actually late for a meeting, huh?

147
00:06:25,521 --> 00:06:26,360
You're leaving after entering the room.

148
00:06:26,440 --> 00:06:27,120
What's going on?

149
00:06:28,360 --> 00:06:29,521
Nothing's going on.

150
00:06:30,161 --> 00:06:31,680
Nothing's going on? Just look at you.

151
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:32,800
Come on. Let's have lunch.

152
00:06:37,440 --> 00:06:38,360
Hello, Ms. Huang?

153
00:06:41,881 --> 00:06:42,881
Weren't they okay

154
00:06:42,920 --> 00:06:43,881
when I sent them to school this morning?

155
00:06:45,161 --> 00:06:46,000
Alright, understood.

156
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:46,560
I'll go and pick them up.

157
00:06:47,560 --> 00:06:48,161
You see,

158
00:06:48,240 --> 00:06:48,961
something cropped up at home.

159
00:06:49,401 --> 00:06:50,841
The teacher said Cong and Qi are having

160
00:06:50,841 --> 00:06:52,040
gastroenteritis.

161
00:06:53,040 --> 00:06:54,240
Where's Gao Ping, then?

162
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:56,040
You can tell Gao Ping
to check on them.

163
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:57,560
No need for that.

164
00:06:57,721 --> 00:06:59,721
He's preparing for his thesis defense.

165
00:07:00,201 --> 00:07:01,201
He's just making preparations.

166
00:07:01,201 --> 00:07:02,360
It's not like he's doing it.

167
00:07:02,440 --> 00:07:03,161
The children are sick, you know?

168
00:07:03,161 --> 00:07:04,201
He can't just ignore them.

169
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:05,440
It's fine. I'll pick them up myself.

170
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:06,040
That's not it.

171
00:07:06,401 --> 00:07:07,081
How will you head there?

172
00:07:07,161 --> 00:07:08,321
I thought your car broke down.

173
00:07:08,961 --> 00:07:09,841
I'll hire a cab.

174
00:07:09,920 --> 00:07:10,480
It's more convenient.

175
00:07:12,440 --> 00:07:13,120
You can drive my car there.

176
00:07:13,721 --> 00:07:14,600
Yuanyuan and I are here.

177
00:07:14,961 --> 00:07:15,841
Thank you, Boss.

178
00:07:15,841 --> 00:07:16,881
Sorry for making you
entertain them alone.

179
00:07:29,721 --> 00:07:30,440
Cong's mother!

180
00:07:30,480 --> 00:07:31,761
Ms. Huang, how are the children?

181
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:32,480
They've already taken

182
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:33,440
anti-nausea and
anti-diarrhea medication.

183
00:07:33,521 --> 00:07:34,201
For safety's sake,

184
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:35,281
you should take them to the hospital.

185
00:07:35,401 --> 00:07:35,961
Come. Over here.

186
00:07:39,440 --> 00:07:40,721
Cong, Qi.

187
00:07:42,721 --> 00:07:43,961
Are you guys sick?

188
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:46,440
Mom.

189
00:07:46,841 --> 00:07:49,040
Mom, why are you only here now?

190
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:51,120
Mom, I feel terrible.

191
00:07:52,040 --> 00:07:53,480
Your stomach hurts, doesn't it?

192
00:07:54,201 --> 00:07:56,161
I'll take you guys to the hospital now.

193
00:07:56,201 --> 00:07:58,440
The doctors will give you a diagnosis

194
00:07:58,480 --> 00:07:59,401
and tell you why your tummy hurts.

195
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:01,240
Mom, I can't walk.

196
00:08:01,240 --> 00:08:03,161
Can you carry me on your back?

197
00:08:04,281 --> 00:08:05,480
I can carry you on my back.

198
00:08:06,201 --> 00:08:08,560
Mom, I can walk by myself.

199
00:08:08,881 --> 00:08:10,401
You can walk by yourself?

200
00:08:10,480 --> 00:08:11,761
My baby, you're great.

201
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:12,961
Good job.

202
00:08:12,961 --> 00:08:14,281
I'll carry Cong on my back, then.

203
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:16,240
Come.

204
00:08:18,521 --> 00:08:19,360
Come, my baby.

205
00:08:19,961 --> 00:08:21,000
Get up.

206
00:08:28,201 --> 00:08:28,680
Okay.

207
00:08:32,881 --> 00:08:33,641
Ms. Huang, sorry for the trouble.

208
00:08:33,641 --> 00:08:34,401
Let me carry your bag for you.

209
00:08:34,761 --> 00:08:35,560
Thank you.

210
00:08:35,560 --> 00:08:36,161
Qi, let's go.

211
00:08:36,281 --> 00:08:37,241
Baby, let's go.

212
00:08:37,800 --> 00:08:39,241
Be careful.

213
00:08:42,361 --> 00:08:42,761
Here.

214
00:08:42,761 --> 00:08:43,680
I'll open the door for your mother.

215
00:08:58,840 --> 00:08:59,440
(Xiang Zhong: Deng Haiyang,)

216
00:08:59,440 --> 00:09:00,200
(where are you right now?)

217
00:09:19,401 --> 00:09:20,080
(Haiyang: Changsha...)

218
00:09:24,241 --> 00:09:25,560
Why did you go to Changsha?

219
00:09:27,761 --> 00:09:28,161
(Haiyang: Road.)

220
00:09:34,001 --> 00:09:34,720
Buddy,

221
00:09:34,720 --> 00:09:36,361
can't you finish your sentence?

222
00:09:44,040 --> 00:09:45,601
(Medical Technology Center)
You guys are okay now, right?

223
00:09:46,161 --> 00:09:47,761
You guys can enjoy beverages.

224
00:09:48,481 --> 00:09:49,800
The doctor told me

225
00:09:49,881 --> 00:09:51,440
to buy electrolyte water for you.

226
00:09:51,960 --> 00:09:52,720
Mom,

227
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:55,320
why isn't Dad here yet?

228
00:10:00,121 --> 00:10:01,440
Dad...

229
00:10:02,481 --> 00:10:03,680
He's on a business trip.

230
00:10:04,040 --> 00:10:06,080
Who will recharge my battery, then?

231
00:10:06,161 --> 00:10:09,001
I'll be out of energy without it.

232
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:11,960
I'll recharge your battery

233
00:10:11,960 --> 00:10:12,920
after we're done with the drip.

234
00:10:13,601 --> 00:10:15,560
Mom, it's useless when you do it.

235
00:10:16,001 --> 00:10:18,560
Can you stop talking?

236
00:10:22,800 --> 00:10:23,920
You guys will be energetic

237
00:10:23,920 --> 00:10:24,920
after taking the drip.

238
00:10:41,320 --> 00:10:42,840
I'm here. Where are you?

239
00:10:43,440 --> 00:10:44,281
I saw you.

240
00:10:44,840 --> 00:10:45,761
I didn't see you.

241
00:10:46,361 --> 00:10:47,560
Look at your left rear at a 45Â° angle.

242
00:10:56,401 --> 00:10:57,720
You're wearing spectacles now.

243
00:10:57,800 --> 00:10:59,361
Do you have shortsightedness
or presbyopia?

244
00:10:59,800 --> 00:11:00,560
It's none of them.

245
00:11:01,040 --> 00:11:02,121
It's just a decoration.

246
00:11:02,761 --> 00:11:03,601
You changed your style, huh?

247
00:11:03,761 --> 00:11:04,641
You look refined now.

248
00:11:04,881 --> 00:11:05,320
Yeah, right?

249
00:11:06,960 --> 00:11:07,440
Why don't we take a walk?

250
00:11:08,121 --> 00:11:08,881
Alright. Let's go.

251
00:11:09,881 --> 00:11:10,960
What are you doing in Shanghai?

252
00:11:11,521 --> 00:11:12,121
To attend a training program.

253
00:11:12,521 --> 00:11:13,241
What training program?

254
00:11:13,881 --> 00:11:15,521
A training program for
Odor Detection Specialists.

255
00:11:16,401 --> 00:11:17,800
What's an Odor Detection Specialist?

256
00:11:18,560 --> 00:11:20,560
An odor detection specialist

257
00:11:20,761 --> 00:11:21,761
will determine

258
00:11:22,080 --> 00:11:22,800
whether an environment

259
00:11:23,241 --> 00:11:23,881
or a water source

260
00:11:23,920 --> 00:11:24,720
is polluted or not
and its pollution level

261
00:11:24,800 --> 00:11:25,881
by using their sense of smell.

262
00:11:26,440 --> 00:11:27,481
That's a new position

263
00:11:27,560 --> 00:11:28,560
added to our
environmental protection system.

264
00:11:30,761 --> 00:11:31,960
It's not just us. It includes you guys.

265
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:34,840
Listen,

266
00:11:34,881 --> 00:11:36,481
An odor detection specialist

267
00:11:36,680 --> 00:11:38,401
is also called an olfactory specialist.

268
00:11:38,680 --> 00:11:40,080
We need to take a
professional certificate exam for this.

269
00:11:40,440 --> 00:11:41,840
It's not something that anyone can do.

270
00:11:41,960 --> 00:11:42,800
You have to be talented.

271
00:11:44,080 --> 00:11:45,040
You mean a talent for odor detection?

272
00:11:45,800 --> 00:11:47,361
Olfactory talent.

273
00:11:48,521 --> 00:11:49,881
When I attended the test,

274
00:11:50,281 --> 00:11:52,720
I realized that I was much better
than other people.

275
00:11:53,560 --> 00:11:54,601
I suddenly realized

276
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:56,960
that everyone has their own talents.

277
00:11:57,161 --> 00:11:58,601
It's just that they haven't
been discovered yet.

278
00:11:59,920 --> 00:12:01,361
I have to congratulate you, then.

279
00:12:01,440 --> 00:12:02,040
You've finally discovered

280
00:12:02,080 --> 00:12:02,920
your talent.

281
00:12:03,800 --> 00:12:05,001
